[]}, {"name": "oslo_limit.tests.test_limit.TestEnforcerUtils.test_get_limit_no_cache", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.tests.test_limit.TestEnforcerUtils.test_get_limit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit", "documentation": ["Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\"); you may", "not use this file except in compliance with the License. You may obtain", "a copy of the License at", "http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0", "Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software", "distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS, WITHOUT", "WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. See the", "License for the specific language governing permissions and limitations", "under the License."], "functions": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit._get_keystone_connection", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit.CONF", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit.LOG", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._SDK_CONNECTION", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit.ProjectUsage", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._MODELS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit.Enforcer", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit.Enforcer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "usage_callback", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cache", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["An object for checking usage against resource limits and requests.\n\n```\nparam usage_callback\n\nA callable function that accepts a project_id\nstring as a parameter and calculates the current\nusage of a resource.\n\ntype usage_callback\n\ncallable function\n\nparam cache\n\nWhether to cache resource limits for the lifetime of this\nenforcer. Defaults to True.\n\ntype cache\n\nboolean\n```\n"]}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit.Enforcer._get_enforcement_model", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Query keystone for the configured enforcement model."]}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit.Enforcer._get_model_impl", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "usage_callback", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cache", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["get the enforcement model based on configured model in keystone."]}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit.Enforcer.enforce", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "deltas", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check resource usage against limits for resources in deltas\n\nFrom the deltas we extract the list of resource types that need to\nhave limits enforced on them.\n\nFrom keystone we fetch limits relating to this project_id (if\nnot None) and the endpoint specified in the configuration.\n\nUsing the usage_callback specified when creating the enforcer,\nwe fetch the existing usage.\n\nWe then add the existing usage to the provided deltas to get\nthe total proposed usage. This total proposed usage is then\ncompared against all appropriate limits that apply.\n\nNote if there are no registered limits for a given resource type,\nwe fail the enforce in the same way as if we defaulted to\na limit of zero, i.e. do not allow any use of a resource type\nthat does not have a registered limit.\n\nNote that if a project_id of None is provided, we just compare\nagainst the registered limits (i.e. use this for\nnon-project-scoped limits)\n\n```\nparam project_id\n\nThe project to check usage and enforce limits\nagainst (or None).\n\ntype project_id\n\nstring\n\nparam deltas\n\nAn dictionary containing resource names as keys and\nrequests resource quantities as positive integers.\nWe only check limits for resources in deltas.\nSpecify a quantity of zero to check current usage.\n\ntype deltas\n\ndictionary\n\nraises exception.ClaimExceedsLimit\n\nwhen over limits\n```\n"]}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit.Enforcer.calculate_usage", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Calculate resource usage and limits for resources_to_check.\n\nFrom the list of resources_to_check, we collect the project's\nlimit and current usage for each, exactly like we would for\nenforce(). This is useful for reporting current project usage\nand limits in a situation where enforcement is not desired.\n\nThis should *not* be used to conduct custom enforcement, but\nrather only for reporting.\n\n```\nparam project_id\n\nThe project for which to check usage and limits,\nor None.\n\ntype project_id\n\nstring\n\nparam resources_to_check\n\nA list of resource names to query.\n\ntype resources_to_check\n\nlist\n\nreturns\n\nA dictionary of name:limit.ProjectUsage for the\nrequested names against the provided project.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit.Enforcer.get_registered_limits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit.Enforcer.get_project_limits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._FlatEnforcer", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit._FlatEnforcer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "usage_callback", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cache", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._FlatEnforcer.get_registered_limits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._FlatEnforcer.get_project_limits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._FlatEnforcer.get_project_usage", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._FlatEnforcer.enforce", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "deltas", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit._FlatEnforcer.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._StrictTwoLevelEnforcer", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit._StrictTwoLevelEnforcer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "usage_callback", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cache", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._StrictTwoLevelEnforcer.get_registered_limits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._StrictTwoLevelEnforcer.get_project_limits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._StrictTwoLevelEnforcer.get_project_usage", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resources_to_check", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._StrictTwoLevelEnforcer.enforce", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "project_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "deltas", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit._StrictTwoLevelEnforcer.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "oslo_limit.limit._LimitNotFound", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "oslo_limit.limit._LimitNotFound.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resource", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documen